    <div class="content-section">
        <section id="Siddheshwar Temple" class="section">
            <h2>Siddheshwar Temple</h2>
            <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="Siddheshwar Temple" class="section-image">
            <p>The Shri Siddheshwar Temple in Solapur is a significant Hindu temple dedicated to Lord Siddheshwar, an incarnation of Lord Shiva and Lord Vishnu. It's known for its unique location in the middle of a lake and the legend associated with the temple's construction and the saint who established it, Shri Siddharameshwar Maharaj. The temple is a major pilgrimage site in Solapur, and it's believed that the saint aimed to unite followers of Shiva and Vishnu, according to the Department of Tourism Maharashtra. </p>
            <p></p>
        </section>

        <section id="Bhuikot Fort" class="section">
            <h2>Bhuikot Fort</h2>
            <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="Bhuikot Fort" class="section-image">
            <p>Bhuikot Fort, also known as Solapur Fort, is a historical landmark in Solapur, Maharashtra, built during the 14th century by the Bahamani Sultans. It has seen the rule of various dynasties including the Mughals and the Peshwas. The fort is known for its animal park, amusement facilities, and an octagonal well. It is a popular destination for families and those seeking a blend of history and nature. </p>
            <p></p>
        </section>

        <section id="Great Indian Bustard Sanctuary" class="section">
            <h2>Great Indian Bustard Sanctuary</h2>
            <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="Great Indian Bustard Sanctuary" class="section-image">
            <p>The Great Indian Bustard Sanctuary in Solapur, also known as the Jawaharlal Nehru Bustard Sanctuary, is a protected area dedicated to conserving the endangered Great Indian Bustard. Established in 1979, it spans parts of Solapur and Ahmednagar districts, with headquarters at Nannaj in Solapur and Rehekuri in Ahmednagar. The sanctuary is known for its semi-arid grassland habitat and is a crucial breeding and wintering site for the bustard. </p>
            <p></p>
        </section>

        <section id="Solapur Science Centre" class="section">
            <h2>Solapur Science Centre</h2>
            <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="Solapur Science Centre" class="section-image">
            <p>The Solapur Science Centre is a place where visitors can explore and learn about various scientific concepts through interactive exhibits. It is open daily, except Mondays, from 10:00 AM to 5:30 PM. The center is known for its simple and easy-to-understand explanations of scientific principles. </p>
        </section>

        <section id="Saraf Katta" class="section">
            <h2>Saraf Katta</h2>
            <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="Saraf Katta" class="section-image">
            <p>Saraf Katta in Solapur is a popular shopping area, specifically known for textiles like chaddars (cotton sheets) and towels. It's mentioned as one of the "best shopping places" in Solapur. The area is also associated with the sale of various items, as indicated by listings on OLX India. </p>
            <p></p>
        </section>

        <section id="Dharmaveer Sambhaji Lake" class="section">
            <h2>Dharmaveer Sambhaji Lake</h2>
            <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="Dharmaveer Sambhaji Lake" class="section-image">
            <p>Dharmaveer Sambhaji Talav (Lake) is a popular tourist attraction in Shivshahi, Solapur, Maharashtra, according to Justdial. It's located in Pramod Nagar, near Vijapur Road, and is rated 4.1217 by visitors. The lake is one of several notable spots in Shivshahi, alongside places like Shivraj Sagar Target, Kamar Talab, and Bhuikot Fort. Solapur itself is known for its diverse culture, religious sites like Shri Siddheshwar Temple, and as a major textile hub. </p>
            <p></p>
        </section>

        <section id="Hipparga Lake" class="section">
            <h2>Hipparga Lake</h2>
            <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="Hipparga Lake" class="section-image">
            <p>Hipparga Lake, also known as Ekrukh Lake, is a significant water reservoir located near Solapur, Maharashtra, India. It was established in 1871 during British rule and serves as a major source of water for the region, providing irrigation and domestic water supply. The lake is known for its historical significance and ecological importance, and is a popular spot for nature enthusiasts. </p>
            <p></p>
        </section>

        <section id="Akkalkot Swami Samarth Maharaj Temple" class="section">
            <h2>Akkalkot Swami Samarth Maharaj Temple</h2>
            <img src="https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcQR3diFl0Vy4Da60ezSIQtV5qOZ8NQ7ELShSg&s" alt="Akkalkot Swami Samarth Maharaj Temple" class="section-image">
            <p>Akkalkot, a town in the Solapur district of Maharashtra, is renowned as a pilgrimage site centered around the revered saint Shri Swami Samarth Maharaj. He is considered an incarnation of Lord Dattatreya, and is believed to be a reincarnation of Narasimha Saraswati. The town attracts devotees seeking blessings and spiritual solace at the temple dedicated to Swami Samarth. </p>
        </section>

        <section id="Shri Vitthal Rukmini Temple" class="section">
            <h2>Shri Vitthal Rukmini Temple</h2>
            <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="Shri Vitthal Rukmini Temple" class="section-image">
            <p>The Shri Vitthal Rukmini Mandir, located in Pandharpur, Solapur, is a highly revered Hindu temple dedicated to Lord Vitthal (an incarnation of Vishnu) and his consort Rukmini (Goddess Lakshmi). It's considered the spiritual capital of Maharashtra and attracts millions of pilgrims annually. </p>
            <p></p>
        </section>

        <section id=" Ujjani Dam" class="section">
            <h2> Ujjani Dam</h2>
            <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt=" Ujjani Dam" class="section-image">
            <p>Ujjani Dam, also known as Bhima Dam, is a large multipurpose dam located on the Bhima River in Solapur, Maharashtra. It was commissioned in June 1980 and is known for its scenic beauty and the reservoir it creates, which serves various purposes. </p>
            <p></p>
        </section>
